programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: This week, memory meets mission as contestants face off in a high-stakes Kim’s Game challenge—designed to sharpen recall under pressure with 100 points and team leadership on the line. With observation, speed, and accuracy all in play, remembering every detail could make or break the mission. As the team pushes forward, it’s time to dig deeper. Contestants open up about their backstories, revealing the powerful personal reasons that brought them to the toughest reality show on earth. Some are here to prove something. Others? To fight for more than just themselves. The action intensifies as Hoffner Knives returns with a brutal tactical evolution, testing shooting and blade skills with precision under pressure. A split-second difference determines the winner of a major reward—proving that in this game, every tenth of a second matters. The day wraps with a visit from HCA Precision Barrels and one final classroom lesson—a pointed reminder that in the world of elite operators, your story is your strength… or your downfall.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: Back by unpopular demand, the infamous “Blah Line” returns—and it’s more brutal than ever. The contestants kick off the day with a hellish PT session that leaves bodies broken and spirits tested. Things only get rougher from there with a punishing stealth crawl over jagged rocks, grinding them down before they face Ken Shamrock’s infamous Lion’s Den training—a relentless gauntlet of pain, grit, and raw endurance. As Don Mann continues to forge a battle-ready team, the squad is thrown into breaching drills designed for high-stakes mission execution. It’s chaos, it’s calculated, and it separates the contenders from the pretenders. In the heat of the action, two standouts emerge from the ranks—earning the coveted role of designated breachers.

In its heyday it was home to vicious criminals, and sadistic guards. Hangings, whippings and torture were daily affairs and spirits from that era still linger on in the maze of cell blocks and corridors. Many male criminals were hanged at the Northwest Mounted Police outpost known as Fort Saskatchewan, but only one woman. programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Chokehold: Busting Boston's Mob
programme.desc: FBI agent Vince delaMontaigne infiltrates the powerful La Cosa Nostra mob in an attempt to break their stranglehold on organized crime in Boston. To do this, delaMontaigne befriends Biagio DiGiacomo in the restaurant he owns and becomes one of the regulars who make deals and plot various ways to make a dishonest dollar. His efforts finally pay off but not before he's entangled in illegal betting, drug sales and extortion simply by playing his undercover role so well and being in the right place at the right time.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Chokehold: Busting Boston's Mob
programme.desc: FBI agent Vince delaMontaigne infiltrates the powerful La Cosa Nostra mob in an attempt to break their stranglehold on organized crime in Boston. To do this, delaMontaigne befriends Biagio DiGiacomo in the restaurant he owns and becomes one of the regulars who make deals and plot various ways to make a dishonest dollar. His efforts finally pay off but not before he's entangled in illegal betting, drug sales and extortion simply by playing his undercover role so well and being in the right place at the right time.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Chokehold: Busting Boston's Mob
programme.desc: FBI agent Vince delaMontaigne infiltrates the powerful La Cosa Nostra mob in an attempt to break their stranglehold on organized crime in Boston. To do this, delaMontaigne befriends Biagio DiGiacomo in the restaurant he owns and becomes one of the regulars who make deals and plot various ways to make a dishonest dollar. His efforts finally pay off but not before he's entangled in illegal betting, drug sales and extortion simply by playing his undercover role so well and being in the right place at the right time.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Chokehold: Busting Boston's Mob
programme.desc: FBI agent Vince delaMontaigne infiltrates the powerful La Cosa Nostra mob in an attempt to break their stranglehold on organized crime in Boston. To do this, delaMontaigne befriends Biagio DiGiacomo in the restaurant he owns and becomes one of the regulars who make deals and plot various ways to make a dishonest dollar. His efforts finally pay off but not before he's entangled in illegal betting, drug sales and extortion simply by playing his undercover role so well and being in the right place at the right time.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Chokehold: Busting Boston's Mob
programme.desc: FBI agent Vince delaMontaigne infiltrates the powerful La Cosa Nostra mob in an attempt to break their stranglehold on organized crime in Boston. To do this, delaMontaigne befriends Biagio DiGiacomo in the restaurant he owns and becomes one of the regulars who make deals and plot various ways to make a dishonest dollar. His efforts finally pay off but not before he's entangled in illegal betting, drug sales and extortion simply by playing his undercover role so well and being in the right place at the right time.

Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Chokehold: Busting Boston's Mob
programme.desc: FBI agent Vince delaMontaigne infiltrates the powerful La Cosa Nostra mob in an attempt to break their stranglehold on organized crime in Boston. To do this, delaMontaigne befriends Biagio DiGiacomo in the restaurant he owns and becomes one of the regulars who make deals and plot various ways to make a dishonest dollar. His efforts finally pay off but not before he's entangled in illegal betting, drug sales and extortion simply by playing his undercover role so well and being in the right place at the right time.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Chokehold: Busting Boston's Mob
programme.desc: FBI agent Vince delaMontaigne infiltrates the powerful La Cosa Nostra mob in an attempt to break their stranglehold on organized crime in Boston. To do this, delaMontaigne befriends Biagio DiGiacomo in the restaurant he owns and becomes one of the regulars who make deals and plot various ways to make a dishonest dollar. His efforts finally pay off but not before he's entangled in illegal betting, drug sales and extortion simply by playing his undercover role so well and being in the right place at the right time.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Chokehold: Busting Boston's Mob
programme.desc: FBI agent Vince delaMontaigne infiltrates the powerful La Cosa Nostra mob in an attempt to break their stranglehold on organized crime in Boston. To do this, delaMontaigne befriends Biagio DiGiacomo in the restaurant he owns and becomes one of the regulars who make deals and plot various ways to make a dishonest dollar. His efforts finally pay off but not before he's entangled in illegal betting, drug sales and extortion simply by playing his undercover role so well and being in the right place at the right time.
